ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIB.name: ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIB

revisions.description: Modify the following objects: [1] Add a new enum definition in CvAtmSessionProtocol [2] Change the default value in cvAtmPeerCfgInBandSignaling

Add new objects for handling the following: [1] Call History object ids 6-17 to bring MIB inline with stored Call History record. [2] Added Call Active Entry objects [3] Added Dialpeer Objects for VoATM

ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-voice@cisco.com
ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIB.description: This MIB module enhances the IETF Dial Control MIB (RFC2128) by providing ATM management information over a data network.

CvAtmSessionProtocol.name: CvAtmSessionProtocol
CvAtmSessionProtocol.description: Represents a Session Protocol used by Voice calls between a local and remote router via the ATM backbone. other - none of the following. ciscoSwitched - cisco proprietary ATM session protocol.

cvAtmCallHistoryTable.name: cvAtmCallHistoryTable
cvAtmCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the ATM extension to the call history table of IETF Dial Control MIB. It contains ATM call leg information about specific voice over ATM call.

cvAtmCallHistoryEntry.name: cvAtmCallHistoryEntry
cvAtmCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a single ATM call leg. An entry of this table is created when its associated call history entry in the IETF Dial Control MIB is created and the call history entry contains information for the call establishment to the peer on the data network backbone via a voice over ATM peer. Th the IETF Dial Control MIB is deleted.

cvAtmCallHistoryConnectionId.name: cvAtmCallHistoryConnectionId
cvAtmCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the ATM call.

cvAtmCallHistoryVpi.name: cvAtmCallHistoryVpi
cvAtmCallHistoryVpi.description: The VPI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallHistoryVci.name: cvAtmCallHistoryVci
cvAtmCallHistoryVci.description: The VCI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallHistoryLowerIfName.name: cvAtmCallHistoryLowerIfName
cvAtmCallHistoryLowerIfName.description: The ifName of the ATM interface associated with this call.

cvAtmCallHistorySessionTarget.name: cvAtmCallHistorySessionTarget
cvAtmCallHistorySessionTarget.description: The object indicates the session target of the peer that was used for the voice over ATM call. A zero length string indicates that the value is unavailable.

cvAtmCallHistorySubchannelID.name: cvAtmCallHistorySubchannelID
cvAtmCallHistorySubchannelID.description: The subchannel used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallHistorySessionProtocol.name: cvAtmCallHistorySessionProtocol
cvAtmCallHistorySessionProtocol.description: Indicates the session protocol used on this call.

cvAtmCallHistoryCalledNumber.name: cvAtmCallHistoryCalledNumber
cvAtmCallHistoryCalledNumber.description: Indicates the called party number for trunk connection calls. A zero length string indicates that this data is unavailable.

cvAtmCallHistoryDtmfRelay.name: cvAtmCallHistoryDtmfRelay
cvAtmCallHistoryDtmfRelay.description: Indicates if Dtmf Relay was enabled for the call.

cvAtmCallHistoryUseSeqNumbers.name: cvAtmCallHistoryUseSeqNumbers
cvAtmCallHistoryUseSeqNumbers.description: Indicates if Sequence Numbers were used on the voice data packets.

cvAtmCallActiveTable.name: cvAtmCallActiveTable
cvAtmCallActiveTable.description: This table is the ATM extension to the active call table of IETF Dial Control MIB. It contains ATM call leg information about specific voice over ATM call.

cvAtmCallActiveEntry.name: cvAtmCallActiveEntry
cvAtmCallActiveEntry.description: The information regarding a single ATM call leg. An entry of this table is created when its associated call active entry in the IETF Dial Control MIB is created. The call active entry contains information for the call establishment to the peer on the data network backbone via a voice over ATM peer. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the IETF Dial Control MIB is deleted.

cvAtmCallActiveConnectionId.name: cvAtmCallActiveConnectionId
cvAtmCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the ATM call.

cvAtmCallActiveVpi.name: cvAtmCallActiveVpi
cvAtmCallActiveVpi.description: The VPI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallActiveVci.name: cvAtmCallActiveVci
cvAtmCallActiveVci.description: The VCI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallActiveLowerIfName.name: cvAtmCallActiveLowerIfName
cvAtmCallActiveLowerIfName.description: The ifName of the ATM interface associated with this call.

cvAtmCallActiveSessionTarget.name: cvAtmCallActiveSessionTarget
cvAtmCallActiveSessionTarget.description: The object indicates the session target of the peer that is used for the voice over ATM call. A null string indicates that the value is unavailable.

cvAtmCallActiveSubchannelID.name: cvAtmCallActiveSubchannelID
cvAtmCallActiveSubchannelID.description: The subchannel used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmCallActiveSessionProtocol.name: cvAtmCallActiveSessionProtocol
cvAtmCallActiveSessionProtocol.description: Indicates the session protocol being used on this call.

cvAtmCallActiveCalledNumber.name: cvAtmCallActiveCalledNumber
cvAtmCallActiveCalledNumber.description: Indicates the called party number for trunk connection calls. A null string indicates that this data is unavailable.

cvAtmCallActiveDtmfRelay.name: cvAtmCallActiveDtmfRelay
cvAtmCallActiveDtmfRelay.description: Indicates if Dtmf Relay is enabled for the call.

cvAtmCallActiveUseSeqNumbers.name: cvAtmCallActiveUseSeqNumbers
cvAtmCallActiveUseSeqNumbers.description: Indicates if Sequence Numbers are used on the voice data packets.

cvAtmPeerCfgTable.name: cvAtmPeerCfgTable
cvAtmPeerCfgTable.description: The table contains the Voice over ATM (ATM) peer specific information that is required to accept or place voice calls via the ATM backbone with the session protocol specified in cvAtmPeerCfgSessionProtocol.

cvAtmPeerCfgEntry.name: cvAtmPeerCfgEntry
cvAtmPeerCfgEntry.description: A single ATM specific Peer. One entry per ATM encapsulation. The entry is created when its associated 'voiceOverATM(152)' encapsulation ifEntry is created. This entry is deleted when its associated ifEntry is deleted.

cvAtmPeerCfgSessionProtocol.name: cvAtmPeerCfgSessionProtocol
cvAtmPeerCfgSessionProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for Internet call between local and remote router via ATM backbone.

cvAtmPeerCfgInterfaceName.name: cvAtmPeerCfgInterfaceName
cvAtmPeerCfgInterfaceName.description: The object specifies the ifName on which the call will go out. A zero length string indicates that no interface has been assigned.

cvAtmPeerCfgVpi.name: cvAtmPeerCfgVpi
cvAtmPeerCfgVpi.description: The VPI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmPeerCfgVci.name: cvAtmPeerCfgVci
cvAtmPeerCfgVci.description: The VCI used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmPeerCfgVcName.name: cvAtmPeerCfgVcName
cvAtmPeerCfgVcName.description: The VC Name used for this ATM connection.

cvAtmPeerCfgCoderRate.name: cvAtmPeerCfgCoderRate
cvAtmPeerCfgCoderRate.description: This object specifies the default voice coder rate of speech for the ATM peer.

cvAtmPeerCfgCodecBytes.name: cvAtmPeerCfgCodecBytes
cvAtmPeerCfgCodecBytes.description: This object specifies the payload size for the voice packets to be transmitted during the call.

cvAtmPeerCfgFaxRate.name: cvAtmPeerCfgFaxRate
cvAtmPeerCfgFaxRate.description: This object specifies the default transmit rate of FAX for the ATM peer. If the value of this object is 'none', then the Fax relay feature is disabled; otherwise the Fax relay feature is enabled.

cvAtmPeerCfgFaxBytes.name: cvAtmPeerCfgFaxBytes
cvAtmPeerCfgFaxBytes.description: This object specifies the payload size for the fax packets to be transmitted during the call.

cvAtmPeerCfgInBandSignaling.name: cvAtmPeerCfgInBandSignaling
cvAtmPeerCfgInBandSignaling.description: This object specifies the type of in-band signaling used between the two end points of the call and is used by the router to determine how to interpret the ABCD signaling bits sent as part of the voice payload data.

cvAtmPeerCfgVADEnable.name: cvAtmPeerCfgVADEnable
cvAtmPeerCfgVADEnable.description: This object specifies whether or not VAD (Voice Activity Detection) is enabled. If the object value is 'false', then the voice data is continuously transmitted to ATM backbone.

cvAtmPeerCfgUseSeqNumbers.name: cvAtmPeerCfgUseSeqNumbers
cvAtmPeerCfgUseSeqNumbers.description: This object specifies whether or not Sequence Numbers are generated on voice packets.

cvAtmPeerCfgDtmfRelay.name: cvAtmPeerCfgDtmfRelay
cvAtmPeerCfgDtmfRelay.description: This object specifies whether or not Dtmf Relay is enabled. If it is then dtmf digits are transported as FRF11 Annex C packets, instead of being encoded as speech.

ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIBCompliance.name: ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIBCompliance
ciscoVoiceAtmDialControlMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO VOICE ATM DIAL CONTROL MIB

cvAtmCallHistoryGroup.name: cvAtmCallHistoryGroup
cvAtmCallHistoryGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ATM Call History entry capability.

cvAtmCallActiveGroup.name: cvAtmCallActiveGroup
cvAtmCallActiveGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ATM Call Active entry capability.

cvAtmPeerCfgGroup.name: cvAtmPeerCfgGroup
cvAtmPeerCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ATM Dialpeer capability. These objects have been implemented as read-only.
